{"TopicId":152358,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Motorized Landing Gear?","CreatedByName":"TheEpicSquared","CreatedById":158667,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-21T13:30:07Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"TheEpicSquared","CreatedById":158667,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-21T13:30:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was just thinking the other day when I was taxiing my passenger plane to the runway. I was thinking, it would be really useful if the landing gears had motors in them so we don\u0027t have to use our engines (and therefore expend fuel) to taxi to a specific location.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLet\u0027s say you sent a resupply \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E to Duna, but you overshot the base. It would be much better\u00A0to use in-built motors to taxi to the base, instead of expending valuable \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Liquid Fuel and Oxidizer\u0022\u003ELFO\u003C/abbr\u003E just to travel a kilometer or so.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course, the motors would use electric charge and have maximum loads, much like actual rover wheels in KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo what do you think? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-21T13:34:58Z\u0022 title=\u002211/21/2016 01:34  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 21, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by TheEpicSquared\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DrunkenKerbalnaut","CreatedById":169550,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-21T14:05:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not opposed to this, but in the interim, you could always build one of these guys with ruggedized rover wheels:\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022taxibot-iai-01.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://media.treehugger.com/assets/images/2013/02/taxibot-iai-01.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sharpy","CreatedById":145504,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-21T14:21:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222859041\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479737101\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022169550\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DrunkenKerbalnaut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, DrunkenKerbalnaut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not opposed to this, but in the interim, you could always build one of these guys with ruggedized rover wheels:\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022taxibot-iai-01.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://media.treehugger.com/assets/images/2013/02/taxibot-iai-01.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLanding gear with a docking port?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DrunkenKerbalnaut","CreatedById":169550,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-21T14:24:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222859058\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479738088\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022145504\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sharpy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Sharpy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLanding gear with a docking port?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr find a way to hook the nose gear with something. But yeah docking port jr\u00A0should do the trick. One on the planes \u0022chin\u0022, and another above the rovers \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-21T14:24:40Z\u0022 title=\u002211/21/2016 02:24  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 21, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by DrunkenKerbalnaut\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003ESpeeling\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wallace","CreatedById":77574,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-21T14:26:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I did when I made a powered glider/rover for duna was, I have it landing gear and rover wheels on the front, the landing gear sticks lower than the rover wheels so it can land on that, then I retract the front landing gear so the rover wheels touch the ground and can drive around, then for take off again, I put the landing gear down again.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022sjQSOZ1.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022505\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/sjQSOZ1.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DrunkenKerbalnaut","CreatedById":169550,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-21T14:30:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222859068\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479738378\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002277574\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Wallace\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Wallace said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I did when I made a powered glider/rover for duna was, I have it landing gear and rover wheels on the front, the landing gear sticks lower than the rover wheels so it can land on that, then I retract the front landing gear so the rover wheels touch the ground and can drive around, then for take off again, I put the landing gear down again.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/sjQSOZ1.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022sjQSOZ1.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022505\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/sjQSOZ1.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDisregard my solution. This guy\u00A0knows how to Kerbal. That\u0027s how I make my forklifts \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheEpicSquared","CreatedById":158667,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-21T17:03:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222859068\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479738378\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002277574\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Wallace\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Wallace said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat I did when I made a powered glider/rover for duna was, I have it landing gear and rover wheels on the front, the landing gear sticks lower than the rover wheels so it can land on that, then I retract the front landing gear so the rover wheels touch the ground and can drive around, then for take off again, I put the landing gear down again.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/sjQSOZ1.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022sjQSOZ1.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022505\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/sjQSOZ1.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI often do that as well, but the problem with that is that the motorized wheels create a lot of drag. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NeoFatalis","CreatedById":153893,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-21T17:09:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I remember correctly there was once a mod called adjustable landing gear and it had an option of motorized wheels altough it is broken since 1.1 because of the wheels update\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheEpicSquared","CreatedById":158667,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-21T17:27:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222859240\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479748162\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153893\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NeoFatalis\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, NeoFatalis said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I remember correctly there was once a mod called adjustable landing gear and it had an option of motorized wheels altough it is broken since 1.1 because of the wheels update\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, I could never get that to work \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"juanml82","CreatedById":105344,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-23T23:33:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would also work great for storing rovers in cargo bays, since motorized landing gear can be used for rovers and it\u0027s retractable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI usually try to set the wheels wide and give some clearance for the rest of the rover, and the resulting design won\u0027t fit an MK3 cargo bay. With retractable motorized landing gears, they\u0027d fit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rath","CreatedById":138223,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-24T01:36:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMotorized landing gear should be pretty slow and big, so that they dont replace normal wheels\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scientia1423","CreatedById":116562,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-24T06:20:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222859065\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479738249\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022169550\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DrunkenKerbalnaut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/21/2016 at 2:24 PM, DrunkenKerbalnaut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr find a way to hook the nose gear with something. But yeah docking port jr\u00A0should do the trick. One on the planes \u0022chin\u0022, and another above the rovers \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUse the AGU to dock with the plane. But what if my plane has no chin?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso the idea seems to be a good one. I have trouble driving rovers as the landing gear is not motorised.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DrunkenKerbalnaut","CreatedById":169550,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-24T14:41:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222862746\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221479968413\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022116562\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scientia1423\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Scientia1423 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut what if my plane has no chin?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMk1 or mk2 (depending in which profile you are using) shielded docking port at planes \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E, facing down.\u00A0Then another on top of rover \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E. Like the way people move surface base pieces.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wyzard","CreatedById":162363,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-24T17:48:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you use \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/142594-12-kerbal-attachment-system-kas-v060/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/a\u003E, you can put a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E attachment point on the front of your plane, and a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E winch on the back of a rover, and connect the winch cable to tow the plane.\u00A0 If your base has \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E, you can use the same attachment point to connect a fuel hose to refuel the plane.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheEpicSquared","CreatedById":158667,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-24T19:31:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222863219\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022152358\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221480009730\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022162363\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Wyzard\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Wyzard said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you use \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/142594-12-kerbal-attachment-system-kas-v060/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/a\u003E, you can put a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E attachment point on the front of your plane, and a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E winch on the back of a rover, and connect the winch cable to tow the plane.\u00A0 If your base has \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E, you can use the same attachment point to connect a fuel hose to refuel the plane.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, that\u0027s how I do it currently.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}